	(2)


	          


	Crude oils can
	also be classified by sulfur content (by weight).  Sour crudes contain 0.5% or greater sulfur
	content (by weight) and sweet crudes contain less than 0.5% sulfur content
	(by weight).  Substantially all of our
	exports are classified as sour crude.




	 




